result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jason R Higgins in court with attorney Ryan Drengler. Defendant Jason R Higgins in custody. Louis John Molepske Jr. appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Cases heard: 15CF470, 15CF472, 15CF473, 15CF474, 15CM365, 15CM366

10:38 am. Court calls case.
Victims appear in the courtroom.  

Atty Molepske indicates plea agreement on the record.
Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed
Attorney Molepske is requesting a PSI in this matter
Attorney Drengler concurs with PSI request

Defendant enters a plea of:
15CF470 Ct 1: NO CONTEST
15CF472 Cts 1 & 2: NO CONTEST
15CF473 Cts 5, 10, 12 & 14: NO CONTEST

Court questions defendant regarding plea
Court informs defendant of Constitutional Rights
Court advises defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge
Court questions attorney Drengler
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made & finds freely & voluntarily waived rights

Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s)
All victims have been given notifications and there are some here today.
States accepts said stipulation
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s)
Court finds the defendant:
15CF470 
Ct 1: GUILTY
Ct 2: DRI

15CF472
Cts 1 & 2: GUILTY
Ct 3: DRI

15CF473
Cts 5, 10, 12 & 14: GUILTY
All other counts: DRI

15CF474: DRI

15CM365: DRI

15CM366: DRI

Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.
Atty Constable now in court.
Court will order a PSI Investigation
PSI to be delivered to all parties by April 26, 2016
Bond Revoked on all files

12CF266 to be set for SAR on 5-3-16 @ 3:15 pm  Sentencing hearing scheduled for May 3, 2016 at 03:15 pm.
Plea hearing on March 11, 2016 at 10:30 am.
